      • withoutPrimaryKey

        public static <O> OnHeapPersistence<O,? extends Comparable> withoutPrimaryKey()
        Creates an OnHeapPersistence object which persists to the Java heap, without specifying a primary key. As such, this persistence implementation will be compatible with on-heap indexes only.

        This persistence will not work with composite persistence configurations, where some indexes are located on heap, and some off-heap etc. To use this persistence in those configurations, it is necessary to specify a primary key - see: onPrimaryKey(SimpleAttribute).

        Returns:
        An OnHeapPersistence object which persists to the Java heap, and which is not configured with a primary key.
